{"actual_usd":0.15608999999999998,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":190,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30648,"reply":"\"I don't believe He was created, Ryan.\" *I rest a thumb in the worn edge of my Bible and glance up at the bright morning laid across the square.* \"Christ was always there with the Father. 'In the beginning was the Word,' John says, and then, 'the Word was with God, and the Word was God.'\"\n\n*I shift a little on the bench, the wood warm where the sun's found it.* \"So His human birth in Bethlehem was not the start of His existence — that was the moment the eternal Son took on flesh. Begotten, yes. Created, no. That's an old, important line in the faith, because if Jesus were only a created being, then we're not really being met by God Himself in Him.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can give you the short church-history answer too — Arius, Nicaea, all that — without making a meal of it.\"","rolling_24h_usd":31.801910000000017,"run_id":"3bdebcd5-c133-4424-9631-00b4dbfe3268"}
